The paper deals with the problem of false data injection attacks in the smart grid, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The proposed method involves statistical learning techniques such as the Conditional Covariance Test (CCT) and correlation anomaly score, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the DC power flow model, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SY and cs.CR, followed by cs.AI, cs.NI, and cs.DC.
